State MSM Profile: Mississippi

Background & Methods

In 2015-2016, researchers at Emory University partnered with colleagues at the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) to develop methods to estimate the number of men who have sex with men (MSM) residing in each county in the United States. Using population and housing data from the American Community Survey and estimates from two peer-reviewed publications (Oster et al., 2015 & Purcell et al., 2012), they derived an indirect estimate of MSM population sizes that took into account both the urbanicity of the county as well as its density of households with a male householder and a male same-sex partner.

The full methodology is published in the Journal of Medical Internet Research - Public Health and Surveillance:

Grey JA, Bernstein KT, Sullivan PS, Purcell DW, Chesson HW, Gift TL, Rosenberg ES. Estimating the population sizes of men who have sex with men in US states and counties using data from the American Community Survey. JMIR Public Health Surveill 2016;2(1):e14. DOI: 10.2196/publichealth.5365

Overview of MSM in Mississippi

An estimated 18,991 men who have sex with men (MSM) resided in Mississippi in 2013, representing 0.4% of the 4,503,084 MSM in the United States. Of the 1,063,557 adult men of Mississippi, 1.8% had had sex with another man in the past 5 years, which was less than the overall percentage of adult men in the United States who were MSM (3.9%).

Most MSM in Mississippi resided in counties within medium or small metropolitan areas (43.2%). Including both central and fringe counties, 15.0% resided in a large metropolitan area.


Percentage of MSM by urbanicity, United States and Mississippi, 2013

MSM in Mississippi Counties

Among counties or county-equivalent areas in Mississippi, DeSoto County had the largest population of MSM at 2,052, representing 10.8% of all MSM in the state. Walthall County had the highest percentage of MSM among adult men in Mississippi at 4.8%. This was greater than the percentage for Mississippi as a whole, which was 1.8% of adult men.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.



MSM in Mississippi Metropolitan Statistical Areas

Jackson Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Jackson MSA had the largest metropolitan population of MSM in Mississippi at 4,226, or 22.3% of all MSM in the state. Of the 199,170 adult men in Jackson, an estimated 2.1% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Gulfport-Biloxi-Pascagoula Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Gulfport-Biloxi-Pascagoula MSA had a population of 2,872 MSM, or 15.1% of all MSM in Mississippi. Of the 138,549 adult men in Gulfport-Biloxi-Pascagoula, an estimated 2.1% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Memphis Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Memphis MSA overlaps three states: Arkansas, Mississippi and Tennessee. The Mississippi portion of the MSA had 2,849 MSM, or 15.0% of all MSM in the state and 13.1% of the 21,722 MSM in the MSA. Of 87,304 adult men in the Mississippi part of Memphis, 3.3% were MSM. This was less than the overall percentage of MSM among adult men in the MSA, which was 4.7% of adult men (21,722 out of 461,959).

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Hattiesburg Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Hattiesburg MSA had a population of 1,105 MSM, or 5.8% of all MSM in Mississippi. Of the 51,491 adult men in Hattiesburg, an estimated 2.1% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.
